Consider:

p0 -> t1 {e1} [l1,u1] <A> -> p1
p0 -> t2 {e2} [l2,u2] <A> -> p1

This can be reduced to:

p0 -> t1 {e1 | e2} [min(l1,l2),max(u1,u2)] <A> -> p1

This is an abstraction, but here is an exact version:

p0 -> t1 {e1 | e2} [int(e1)*l1 + int(e1)*l2, int(e1)*u1 + int(e2)*u2]  
<A> -> p1


